06:46.160 --> 06:48.320
including some comments on one of his novels

06:48.320 --> 06:49.460
Barefoot in the Head

06:50.060 --> 06:54.260
Well, I'd written a novel called Barefoot in the Head

06:54.260 --> 06:57.060
and it really didn't receive

06:57.920 --> 07:00.000
a very kind initial attention

07:00.000 --> 07:02.340
although the premise was simple enough

07:03.600 --> 07:05.860
Barefoot in the Head was about

07:05.860 --> 07:08.800
the world stopped in its tracks by drugs

07:08.800 --> 07:10.640
This was the late 60s, remember?

07:11.840 --> 07:15.240
When the flower power people had been around

07:15.240 --> 07:19.760
and we had had all this love-in stuff

07:20.720 --> 07:23.320
and towards the end of the 60s

07:23.320 --> 07:27.660
the bills, as we say in England

07:27.660 --> 07:31.220
the checks were coming in for all that kind of stuff

07:31.220 --> 07:33.820
and they were already finding the fetuses

07:33.820 --> 07:36.200
in the trash cans of Haight-Ashbury

07:36.200 --> 07:39.500
so that Barefoot in the Head was an ambivalent book

07:39.500 --> 07:40.920
written in a difficult language

07:48.440 --> 07:55.900
and I was a little surprised at the tepid response it got

07:55.900 --> 07:57.680
the angry response it got

07:57.680 --> 07:58.860
the anonymous letters

07:58.860 --> 08:02.500
so I thought, well, let's be finished with the science fiction field

08:03.680 --> 08:06.440
and I thought, well, before I leave it

08:06.440 --> 08:08.300
I ought to write down

08:08.300 --> 08:10.100
all that I know and love about it

08:11.880 --> 08:12.960
before I forget

08:13.940 --> 08:14.940
and so really

08:14.940 --> 08:16.320
I settled down with that in mind

08:16.320 --> 08:17.560
to write Billion Year Spree

08:17.560 --> 08:19.660
and also to have an argument

08:19.660 --> 08:21.060
as I raised my hat

08:21.060 --> 08:24.640
and left the science fictional community

08:26.220 --> 08:28.720
but by the time I got to the end of the thing

08:28.720 --> 08:30.760
you know, three years had passed

08:30.760 --> 08:34.900
and just writing the book

08:34.900 --> 08:36.900
turned me on to science fiction again

08:37.720 --> 08:39.940
Billion Year Spree is full of Aldiss' personal

08:39.940 --> 08:41.120
but fascinating ideas

08:41.120 --> 08:42.920
One provocative idea

08:42.920 --> 08:44.660
heresy to some science fiction fans

08:44.660 --> 08:46.260
was that Hugo Gernsback

08:46.260 --> 08:47.780
the father of modern science fiction

08:47.780 --> 08:49.680
was a disastrous influence on the field

08:49.680 --> 08:51.780
We asked Aldiss what he meant by that

08:51.780 --> 08:54.120
Well, as you probably know

08:54.120 --> 08:56.280
that I did say something of that sort

08:56.280 --> 08:57.520
and since then

08:57.520 --> 09:00.120
people have been threatening to break my legs

09:00.120 --> 09:00.940
and my arms

09:00.940 --> 09:02.600
and shoot me and hang me

09:02.600 --> 09:05.040
and kick me out of the science fiction field

09:05.040 --> 09:06.980
and all sorts of things like that

09:07.700 --> 09:09.320
but I guess that

09:11.440 --> 09:15.000
what I was worried about

09:15.000 --> 09:16.660
was the way

09:17.460 --> 09:18.520
science fiction

09:18.520 --> 09:20.260
was segregated

09:20.260 --> 09:21.860
by Gernsback

09:21.860 --> 09:23.420
into a magazine

09:23.420 --> 09:26.960
so that if you wanted to find science fiction

09:26.960 --> 09:28.460
you had to go

09:28.460 --> 09:29.580
to a magazine

09:29.580 --> 09:30.340
that had

09:31.520 --> 09:33.180
a name like

09:33.180 --> 09:34.400
Astounding

09:34.400 --> 09:35.420
or Amazing

09:35.420 --> 09:36.880
or Staggering

09:36.880 --> 09:38.000
which had

09:38.000 --> 09:39.800
a huge

09:39.800 --> 09:41.400
three-dimensional title

09:41.400 --> 09:42.600
with rivets in it

09:44.320 --> 09:46.140
that resulted

09:46.140 --> 09:47.600
in a monoculture

09:47.600 --> 09:49.520
and we all know

09:49.520 --> 09:50.760
that there are dangers

09:50.760 --> 09:52.820
in monoculture

09:52.820 --> 09:54.300
and

09:54.300 --> 09:56.040
I simply thought

09:56.040 --> 09:56.380
that

09:56.380 --> 09:57.520
science fiction

09:57.520 --> 09:58.760
would be better

09:58.760 --> 10:00.000
as an

10:00.000 --> 10:01.420
uncaged animal

10:01.420 --> 10:02.120
that could

10:02.120 --> 10:03.520
rove at large

10:03.520 --> 10:04.560
where it would

10:04.560 --> 10:06.380
but

10:06.380 --> 10:07.420
nowadays

10:07.420 --> 10:08.940
people complain

10:08.940 --> 10:10.780
that science fiction

10:10.780 --> 10:11.680
is segregated

10:11.680 --> 10:12.760
and that people

10:12.760 --> 10:13.920
think you're funny

10:13.920 --> 10:14.940
if you read it

10:14.940 --> 10:15.380
and that

10:15.380 --> 10:16.440
it has to have

10:16.440 --> 10:17.280
a special place

10:17.280 --> 10:18.160
in a bookshop

10:18.160 --> 10:19.500
right next to

10:19.500 --> 10:21.020
weirdo cult books

10:21.020 --> 10:21.380
about

10:21.380 --> 10:22.840
flying saucers

10:22.840 --> 10:23.360
or whatever

10:23.360 --> 10:25.860
well my answer to that is

10:25.860 --> 10:26.840
that yes

10:26.840 --> 10:27.780
I agree

10:27.780 --> 10:29.260
I think that's too bad

10:29.260 --> 10:30.780
I think science fiction

10:30.780 --> 10:31.960
is much better than that

10:31.960 --> 10:33.120
but the reason

10:33.120 --> 10:34.300
why it is there

10:34.300 --> 10:35.280
is because

10:35.280 --> 10:36.580
of the segregation

10:36.580 --> 10:37.640
that was introduced

10:37.640 --> 10:39.060
by Hugo Gernsback

10:39.060 --> 10:40.880
that was my argument

10:41.780 --> 10:42.820
anyone seeking

10:42.820 --> 10:43.700
to gain a perspective

10:43.700 --> 10:44.500
on science fiction

10:44.500 --> 10:45.020
and fantasy

10:45.020 --> 10:45.520
should read

10:45.520 --> 10:46.400
Billion Year Spree

10:46.400 --> 10:47.420
a personal

10:47.420 --> 10:48.060
but fascinating

10:48.060 --> 10:48.900
account of the field

10:48.900 --> 10:50.000
