Some might say

19:03.020 --> 19:03.540
It's fantasy

19:03.540 --> 19:04.520
But it's not that either

19:04.520 --> 19:05.800
Aldiss talks about

19:05.800 --> 19:06.520
The inspiration

19:06.520 --> 19:07.440
Behind the book

19:08.460 --> 19:10.200
The model I had

19:11.820 --> 19:14.080
Was a pictorial one

19:14.080 --> 19:15.240
That's often the case

19:16.840 --> 19:18.600
Well in several of my novels

19:18.600 --> 19:24.040
I start from a pictorial beginning

19:24.040 --> 19:27.200
And my pictorial beginnings

19:27.200 --> 19:30.840
With Malacia were the etchings

19:30.840 --> 19:34.020
Which the Italian artist

19:34.020 --> 19:36.580
The Baroque artist GBT Epilo

19:36.580 --> 19:38.720
Made at the end of his life

19:38.720 --> 19:41.240
Towards the end of his life

19:41.240 --> 19:42.240
He retired

19:42.240 --> 19:44.840
And he started

19:44.840 --> 19:47.100
Etching

19:47.100 --> 19:50.760
These mysterious little pictures

19:50.760 --> 19:54.440
Of wizards

19:54.440 --> 19:56.300
Mountebanks

19:57.740 --> 19:59.140
Soldiers

19:59.140 --> 20:01.660
Punchinellos

20:01.660 --> 20:04.620
People being dug out of the ground

20:04.620 --> 20:05.580
From graves

20:07.480 --> 20:08.040
Owls

20:08.660 --> 20:10.340
Serpents burning on altars

20:10.340 --> 20:12.660
All sorts of mysterious symbols

20:12.660 --> 20:14.220
In these lovely little pictures

20:14.220 --> 20:16.420
And no one's actually figured out

20:16.420 --> 20:17.240
What they're meant to be

20:17.240 --> 20:18.600
It's like

20:18.600 --> 20:19.960
A science fictional

20:19.960 --> 20:21.440
Alternative world

20:22.120 --> 20:22.680
Where

20:24.120 --> 20:25.220
Magic rules

20:25.220 --> 20:26.440
I suppose you'd say

20:27.360 --> 20:28.440
And I suppose

20:28.440 --> 20:29.420
That was one of the things

20:29.420 --> 20:30.440
I liked about them

20:31.340 --> 20:31.900
So

20:31.900 --> 20:32.740
I thought

20:32.740 --> 20:33.800
Well if no one else

20:33.800 --> 20:35.420
Can reconstruct

20:35.420 --> 20:36.160
This world

20:36.160 --> 20:37.580
To their satisfaction

20:38.600 --> 20:39.940
I'll have a go at it

20:41.160 --> 20:42.580
And so I started

20:42.580 --> 20:43.680
Writing short stories

20:43.680 --> 20:44.280
Around

20:45.500 --> 20:46.800
The more haunting

20:46.800 --> 20:49.040
Of these etchings

20:49.040 --> 20:49.760
Of Tiepolo's.

20:50.860 --> 20:51.800
Malacia itself

20:51.800 --> 20:52.700
Is a grand city

20:52.700 --> 20:53.320
Which exists

20:53.320 --> 20:53.900
In what appears

20:53.900 --> 20:55.080
To be an alternate universe

20:55.080 --> 20:56.260
Suggestive of Earth's

20:56.260 --> 20:57.020
Ancient past

20:57.020 --> 20:58.340
There is no technology

20:58.340 --> 20:59.040
To speak of

20:59.040 --> 21:00.340
Sorcery of a limited sort

21:00.340 --> 21:01.100
Seems to work

21:01.100 --> 21:02.140
And there are all manner

21:02.140 --> 21:03.140
Of exotic creatures

21:03.140 --> 21:04.300
Such as flying beings

21:04.300 --> 21:05.280
Which resemble humans

21:05.280 --> 21:06.820
The novel's main concern

21:06.820 --> 21:07.320
Is art

21:07.320 --> 21:08.480
An unusual theme

21:08.480 --> 21:09.320
For a science fiction

21:09.320 --> 21:10.180
Or fantasy book

21:10.180 --> 21:11.420
Seemingly more appropriate

21:11.420 --> 21:12.480
For a romantic poet

21:12.480 --> 21:13.580
Aldiss told us

21:13.580 --> 21:14.480
That the theme of art

21:14.480 --> 21:15.760
Came out of a serious illness

21:15.760 --> 21:17.120
He had while writing the book

21:17.120 --> 21:21.180
The effect of this internal complaint

21:21.180 --> 21:23.060
I had this hepatitis

21:26.780 --> 21:28.580
Made me feel that

21:29.620 --> 21:31.000
Well my life span

21:31.000 --> 21:31.660
Was limited

21:32.580 --> 21:34.160
And I had frolicked about

21:34.160 --> 21:34.780
A good deal

21:34.780 --> 21:36.100
And had written some books

21:36.100 --> 21:37.000
That I perhaps

21:37.000 --> 21:38.280
Didn't take as seriously

21:38.280 --> 21:39.220
As I should do

21:40.520 --> 21:41.740
And that what I

21:41.740 --> 21:42.880
dearly loved

21:42.880 --> 21:43.860
Was writing

21:43.860 --> 21:45.740
And that I wanted to make

21:45.740 --> 21:47.240
A statement about art

21:49.300 --> 21:50.480
And really

21:50.480 --> 21:51.720
Malacia is

21:51.720 --> 21:53.180
It's all about art

21:53.180 --> 21:54.480
From the title onwards

21:54.480 --> 21:57.160
If the book has a power

21:57.160 --> 21:59.100
It is

21:59.100 --> 22:01.820
The power of

22:01.820 --> 22:03.620
Meditations on

22:03.620 --> 22:05.720
The nature of art

22:05.720 --> 22:07.380
Which is at once

22:07.380 --> 22:09.360
To transfigure

22:09.360 --> 22:11.460
And at the same time

22:11.460 --> 22:12.500
To petrify

22:12.500 --> 22:13.620
And as you know

22:13.620 --> 22:14.580
Malacia itself

22:14.580 --> 22:14.980
Is

22:14.980 --> 22:17.080
A city-state

22:17.080 --> 22:19.060
Under a curse

22:19.060 --> 22:20.000
Of

22:20.000 --> 22:22.260
Zero change

22:23.540 --> 22:24.920
Well that's like

22:24.920 --> 22:25.600
A work of art

22:25.600 --> 22:26.720
It's like Tiepolo's

22:26.720 --> 22:27.960
Little etchings

22:28.760 --> 22:30.300
They may be forever

22:30.980 --> 22:32.140
Enigmatic to us

22:32.140 --> 22:33.440
But they're forever

22:33.440 --> 22:34.220
Unchanging

22:35.000 --> 22:36.680
The Malacia Tapestry

22:36.680 --> 22:37.660
By one of the masters

22:37.660 --> 22:38.780
Of modern science fiction

22:38.780 --> 22:40.120
A difficult novel

22:40.120 --> 22:40.840
To categorize

22:40.840 --> 22:41.720
But a fascinating one

22:41.720 --> 22:42.140
To read

22:42.140 --> 22:43.160
More with author

